      <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
        <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
        <p>MR. SPEAKER : Order, please.</p>
      </speech>
      <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
        <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
        <p>MR. SPEAKER : Order, please. Before I start the daily routine, I'm obliged to do another Speaker's Ruling this morning.</p>
      </speech>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>PRESENTING AND READING PETITIONS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable member for Sydney River-Mira-Louisbourg.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#26046e64-64ec-438e-96e4-9634df5c8f8c">
          <from>MR. ALFIE MACLEOD</from>
          <p>MR. ALFIE MACLEOD : Mr. Speaker, I beg leave to table a petition entitled Petition to Re-Pave Little Lorraine Road. The operative clause is:</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The petition is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>PRESENTING REPORTS OF COMMITTEES</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of Justice.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#e0b2500d-a2c3-4e83-988f-9949fc163344">
          <from>HON. LENA DIAB</from>
          <p>HON. LENA DIAB : Mr. Speaker, as Chairman of the Committee on Law Amendments, I am directed to report that the committee has met and considered the following bill:</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>Bill No. 16 - Entitled an Act to Appoint the Chief of Protocol. (Hon. Maureen MacDonald)</heading>
        <speech by="#92d3529f-fc39-48c9-9f4a-2854c1214b2e">
          <from>MR. SMITH</from>
          <p>MR. SMITH : Mr. Speaker, today in your gallery, we have with us in the House some very special guests. We have from Scotland, Minister Keith Brown, Transport and Veterans Affairs Minister. With Minister Brown and his delegation we have Martyn McDonald, Private Secretary to the minister; Helen Webster, Second Secretary for Scottish Affairs in Canada; Raymond McGovern, Scottish Development International in Canada; and Colonel Martin Gibson, Chairman of Veterans Scotland.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : Ordered that these bills be read a second time on a future day.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : We welcome all our guests to the gallery and hope that they enjoy this morning's proceedings.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#044d7a53-b109-4393-8fbe-efad8b86a796">
          <from>HON. DIANA WHALEN</from>
          <p>HON. DIANA WHALEN : Thank you very much, Mr. Speaker, I appreciate that, and I just want to draw the attention of the House, and members of the House, to the east gallery where we're joined today by Jennifer MacLeod, who is one of the executives of the MacLeod Lorway Group which is an insurance company, which has a number of offices across the province and employs about 75 Nova Scotians.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <num title="139">RESOLUTION NO. 139</num>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of Communities, Culture and Heritage.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#92d3529f-fc39-48c9-9f4a-2854c1214b2e">
          <from>HON. MAURICE SMITH</from>
          <p>HON. MAURICE SMITH : Mr. Speaker, I hereby give notice that on a future day I shall move the adoption of the following resolution:</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#00b13610-b561-4243-94dd-e76d5546df1c">
          <from>HON. TONY INCE</from>
          <p>HON. TONY INCE : Mr. Speaker, I would also like to draw everyone's attention to the gallery. I would like to introduce Mr. Louis Gannon, the executive director of the Black Cultural Centre. (Applause)</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : I've just been advised by the Clerk that the petition tabled earlier is a photocopy and, therefore, is unacceptable due to the regulations and it will be returned to the honourable member.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : Ordered that this bill be read a second time on a future day.</p>
        </speech>
